### Navigation System
#### 1. **Navigation Buttons (with Icons)**
- Always visible at the left and right edges.
- Styled to be unobtrusive but clear.
- Clickable to move between slides.
- Uses **Feather Icons** for a clean look.
- **All text elements should use the Pretendard font.**

```html
<button id="prev-slide" class="nav-button absolute left-5 top-1/2 transform -translate-y-1/2 bg-theme-button text-theme-text p-3 rounded-full shadow-md hover:bg-theme-button-hover font-pretendard">
    <i data-feather="arrow-left"></i>
</button>
<button id="next-slide" class="nav-button absolute right-5 top-1/2 transform -translate-y-1/2 bg-theme-button text-theme-text p-3 rounded-full shadow-md hover:bg-theme-button-hover font-pretendard">
    <i data-feather="arrow-right"></i>
</button>
```

#### 2. **Keyboard Navigation**
- `Arrow Left (←)`: Move to the previous slide.
- `Arrow Right (→)`: Move to the next slide.
- If at the first or last slide, display a toast notification instead of proceeding further.
- **Animate.css effects** will be used when transitioning slides.

#### 3. **Page Indicator (with Icons)**
- A progress indicator at the bottom of the screen.
- Shows the current slide number out of the total slides.
- Updates dynamically when navigating.
- Uses **Feather Icons** for aesthetics.
- **All text elements should use the Pretendard font.**

```html
<div class="page-indicator absolute bottom-5 left-1/2 transform -translate-x-1/2 bg-theme-indicator text-theme-text px-4 py-2 rounded-full flex items-center space-x-2 font-pretendard">
    <i data-feather="circle"></i>
    <span id="slide-number">1 / X</span>
</div>
```

